cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and machine learning, specifically on learning visual representations from egocentric video. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of unsupervised learning and convolutional neural networks, which are common topics in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of proprioceptive motor signals and autonomous driving platforms, which are relevant to cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
